<br>
From what little I know of MacroQuest, you have the ability to &quot;query&quot; what is on your cursor at any point in time (ie: if your cursor has a smithing hammer, put it here, otherwise, put the item in the auto-equip slot).  So on failures, or alternate products, you can &quot;ask&quot; the cursor what is on it, and then put it someplace specific.<br>
<br>
Also, it seems you are able to search through bags/inventory to find items.  Things don't necessarily have to be in a static place.<br>
<br>
If you still don't quite see how these macros work, or how a macro would be written for some specific thing, why not check out their website -- usually a good place for information.<br>
